Madam '''Prisaal''' was a [[Gender/Legends|female]] individual from the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Ichtor 8]] who lived during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]]. When her husband was killed by [[Pirate/Legends|pirates]], she vowed to take revenge. After pursuing the pirates through twelve [[Sector/Legends|sectors]] and nearly killing them three separate times, she finally tracked them down on [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]]. After she found their hideout,<ref name="SWG:AMMH" /> in [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]],<ref name="SWG_timeline">{{SWG_timeline}}</ref> she hired freelance soldiers to eliminate the murderers.<ref name="SWG:AMMH" />

==Behind the scenes==
Prisaal was mentioned in the [[2003]] [[Star Wars video games|video game]] [[Star Wars Galaxies|''Star Wars Galaxies: An Empire Divided'']], a [[Roleplaying game|massively multiplayer online role-playing game]] developed by [[Sony]] Online Entertainment and published by [[LucasArts]],<ref name="SWG:AMMH" /> prior to its closure on [[December 15]], [[2011]].<ref name="Shutdown">{{SonyCite|url=playerinfo|text=IMPORTANT INFORMATION ABOUT ''STAR WARS'' GALAXIES™}}</ref> "Madam Prisaal of Ichtor 8" was mentioned in the mission "Avenge My Murdered Husband" that was available at [[mission terminal]]s on Tatooine. Prisaal hired the player to kill her husband's murderers. To accomplish this mission, the player had to destroy a small random base and kill several NPC enemies.<ref name="SWG:AMMH" />

